# Kubernetes Troubleshooting Commands 🚀

A practical Kubernetes troubleshooting guide for DevOps Engineers, SREs, Cloud Engineers, and Students.
This repository contains commonly used `kubectl` commands to debug real-world Kubernetes issues.

---

# 📌 Common Kubernetes Issues Covered

* Pods Not Starting
* Service Not Accessible
* Persistent Volume Claim (PVC) Issues
* ConfigMap Key Not Found
* CrashLoopBackOff Status
* ImagePullBackOff Error
* Node Not Ready
* Failed Scheduling
* RBAC Authorization Errors
* Ingress Controller Issues

---

# 1️⃣ Pods Not Starting

## Check Pod Status

```bash
kubectl get pods
```

## Describe Pod

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

## Check Logs

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name>
```

## Multi-Container Pod Logs

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name> -c <container-name>
```

## Watch Pods Live

```bash
kubectl get pods -w
```

---

# 2️⃣ Service Not Accessible

## Check Services

```bash
kubectl get svc
```

## Describe Service

```bash
kubectl describe svc <service-name>
```

## Check Endpoints

```bash
kubectl get endpoints
```

## Verify Pod Labels

```bash
kubectl get pods --show-labels
```

## Test Connectivity Inside Cluster

```bash
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- curl <service-name>
```

---

# 3️⃣ Persistent Volume Claim (PVC) Issues

## Check PVC Status

```bash
kubectl get pvc
```

## Describe PVC

```bash
kubectl describe pvc <pvc-name>
```

## Check Persistent Volumes

```bash
kubectl get pv
```

## Describe Persistent Volume

```bash
kubectl describe pv <pv-name>
```

## Check Storage Classes

```bash
kubectl get sc
```

---

# 4️⃣ ConfigMap Key Not Found

## List ConfigMaps

```bash
kubectl get configmap
```

## Describe ConfigMap

```bash
kubectl describe configmap <configmap-name>
```

## View YAML Output

```bash
kubectl get configmap <configmap-name> -o yaml
```

## Check Pod Events

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

---

# 5️⃣ CrashLoopBackOff Status

## Check Pod Status

```bash
kubectl get pods
```

## Describe Pod

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

## Previous Container Logs

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous
```

## Current Logs

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name>
```

## Watch Restart Count

```bash
kubectl get pods -w
```

---

# 6️⃣ ImagePullBackOff Error

## Describe Pod

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

## Verify Image Name

```bash
kubectl get deployment <deployment-name> -o yaml
```

## Check Secrets

```bash
kubectl get secrets
```

## Verify imagePullSecrets

```bash
kubectl describe serviceaccount default
```

---

# 7️⃣ Node Not Ready

## Check Node Status

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

## Describe Node

```bash
kubectl describe node <node-name>
```

## Check Pods Running on Nodes

```bash
kubectl get pods -A -o wide
```

## Check Node Conditions

```bash
kubectl describe node <node-name> | grep Conditions -A 10
```

---

# 8️⃣ Failed Scheduling

## Check Events

```bash
kubectl get events --sort-by=.metadata.creationTimestamp
```

## Describe Pod

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

## Check Node Resources

```bash
kubectl top nodes
```

## Check Taints

```bash
kubectl describe node <node-name> | grep Taints
```

---

# 9️⃣ RBAC Authorization Errors

## Check Roles

```bash
kubectl get roles
```

## Check RoleBindings

```bash
kubectl get rolebindings
```

## Check ClusterRoles

```bash
kubectl get clusterroles
```

## Check ClusterRoleBindings

```bash
kubectl get clusterrolebindings
```

## Verify User Permissions

```bash
kubectl auth can-i create pods
```

## Check Another User Permission

```bash
kubectl auth can-i delete deployments --as=user1
```

---

# 🔟 Ingress Controller Issues

## Check Ingress Resources

```bash
kubectl get ingress
```

## Describe Ingress

```bash
kubectl describe ingress <ingress-name>
```

## Check Ingress Controller Pods

```bash
kubectl get pods -n ingress-nginx
```

## Check Ingress Controller Logs

```bash
kubectl logs -n ingress-nginx <pod-name>
```

## Check Ingress Services

```bash
kubectl get svc -n ingress-nginx
```

