# 🔥 Master Kubernetes Troubleshooting Commands

These commands help in almost every Kubernetes troubleshooting scenario.

## Get All Resources

```bash
kubectl get all
```

## Describe Any Resource

```bash
kubectl describe <resource> <name>
```

## View Logs

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name>
```

## Check Events

```bash
kubectl get events
```

## View All Pods Across Namespaces

```bash
kubectl get pods -A
```

## Get Pod Details with Node Information

```bash
kubectl get pods -o wide
```

## Cluster Information

```bash
kubectl cluster-info
```

